& [SLMDiffusionRuleTableContract] is the contract for data-driven diffusion rule authority
  + [contract_uuid] is dbe5b6ad-d835-49ce-b5ba-f20e43ac187c
  + [slice_id] is SLM-24
  + [status] is source_implemented_policy_gated

  & [Purpose] is to prevent diffusion behavior from hiding in procedural code
    = must: name every reusable diffusion rule family
    = must: keep rule outputs inside the EvidenceWorkspace until stabilization
    = must: preserve uncertainty instead of forcing role or sense collapse
    - never: let a rule table directly create a stabilized glyph

  & [RuleFamilies] are the v0 extracted rule tables
    + [closed_class_span_rules] form nominal, prepositional, and coordination span candidates
    + [role_pair_span_rules] form compound span candidates from compatible adjacent role evidence
    + [preposition_relation_rules] map preposition subclass evidence to relation candidate kind
    + [sense_coherence_rules] add local support to lexical senses without suppressing competitors

  & [RuntimeProjection] is slm_rust/src/rules.rs
    + [module] is typed Rust rule table authority for the v0 implementation
    + [consumer] is slm_rust/src/diffusion.rs
    + [status] is source_complete_policy_gated
    + [refinement] is SLM-31 closed-class role-pair suppression

  & [DataDrivenBoundary] is the architectural boundary
    = must: diffusion executes rules as evidence pressure
    = must: rule hits produce support, span candidates, or candidate relations
    = must: rule misses preserve candidate evidence for later sidecar deliberation
    - never: treat a rule hit as semantic truth
